	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes and as Lidnariq says, that error shows up (in V3 only, earlier Family BASIC just shows a black screen when no keyboard are connected) because emulators automatically connects the keyboard when detecting one of the Family BASIC ROM hashes. But you can still connect one manually in most emulators if you have hacked the ROM. In most emulators including Nestopia you select it from a menu and in FCEUX you press Scroll Lock.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


