	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What I meant​ was: the hash check isn't preventing the keyboard from working on the modified ROM, it's just automatically enabling it for the unmodified ROM. If you remove the hash check, the keyboard simply won't be automatically enabled for the unmodified ROM anymore, and you'll get the same error message would both ROMs, which doesn't solve your problem. Just enable the keyboard manually.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


